 Click the RESOURCES button at the bottom  Click OK  Set the START TIME  Set the END TIME   Click OK If this will be a recurring appointment  click the RECURRENCE button at the top  Select the RECURRENCE PATTERN  Complete the RANGE OF RECURRENCE  will most likely be  End by  Click the SCHEDULING ASSISTANT button to verify that ALL of the dates times you need are available  If ALL dates times ARE NOT  make the necessary adjusts to your request before proceeding  If ALL dates times ARE available  click the APPOINTMENT button at the top   Click Send You will receive a confirmation email for your reservation NOTE  It is very important that you remember to view the SCHEDULING ASSISTANT to verify that the dates times you want are available BEFORE you  send  your request  If you schedule a recurring appointment and the lab is already reserved on ANY of the dates times you have selected ONLY the dates times that are available will be reserved for you  The unavailable dates WILL NOT be reserved  You will receive a  DECLINED  message advising of the dates that WERE NOT reserved along with the name of the person who actually has them reserved  If you have a day or recurring reservation that you no longer need  please DELETE it from the schedule so someone else can reserve that time  Example  You need to make a recurring reservation for 117 Scott Shipp Lab every Thursday starting at 2 00 p m  and ending at 3 30 p m  beginning on Thursday  March 7 continuing through Thursday  April 25  This lab has already been reserved by someone else on these Thursdays  March 14  March 28  April 18  You  send  your request before viewing the SCHEDULING ASSISTANT to check availability and receive the DECLINED message advising that these three dates are unavailable  You can schedule those three dates in another classroom that is available to you  or you contact the person who has the lab reserved to see if they can make a change  If any of the dates times that were reserved for you are no longer needed  please DELETE them from the schedule so someone else can reserve that time  For instructions please view the Lab Reservations Video  If further assistance is needed  please call 7528  or contact the Help Desk at Help vmi edu or call 7643  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 